 King Williams Town - In a crime intelligence-driven operation the King Williams Town Flying Squad, K9, Ndevana Police members arrested a suspect on Friday afternoon for illegal firearm possession. "Police followed up the information they received about a house at eZintenteni, in Ndevana, that had a firearm," said police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa. "On police arrival, they searched the house and recovered a pistol with seven rounds of ammunition, a police pepper spray and a police emblem star." She said that a 27-year-old male was immediately arrested and charged for possession of unlicensed firearm (pistol) and ammunition and possession of suspected stolen property. "The suspect will appear at Zwelitsha Magistrate's Court on Monday." King William’s Town SAPS Cluster Commander, Brigadier Luntu Ngubelanga, commended the members for the job well done in arresting the suspect and to ensure that he is behind bars. "He also thanked the community for sharing valuable information with SAPS and encouraged them to report any criminal activities to 08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 